narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: French 109 is a great course for motivated students who want to learn to read French. I would absolutely recommend it. It is rigorous, but doing the work is your responsibility. Just doing homework and classwork is not good enough to make you a proficient French reader; you will need to do lots of outside work like Sanjabi recommends. With that in mind, I would recommend the course.
Yes- it is a good course to establish basic reading level in French for research purposes, and the workload is manageable around other courses.
I would recommend this course to anyone, both those already comfortable in their beginning knowledge of French and total neophytes.
A good grammatical introduction to French. Helps if you have some basic French background, requires more effort if you are a true beginner or have no experience with romance languages or Latin
In this course students learn to read French and also gain valuable tools for other language study.
I definitely would recommend this course for those students interested in acquiring professional knowledge from materials written in French.
The class is a great way to amass materials that I will use down the road. I would certainly recommend it as it gives students the tools they need to continue their own course of study.
